The idea is to iterate through all the numbers in the range [l, r], and for each number, check if it is not special. A number is not special if it is a prime, or it has exactly 2 divisors (1 and itself). So, we can count the numbers that are not primes or that have exactly 2 divisors.

Here is the completed code:

```java
public int nonSpecialCount(int l, int r) {
    int res = 0;
    for (int i = l; i <= r; i++) {
        if (i < 2 || PI[i] != PI[i - 1]) {
            res++;
        }
    }
    return res;
}
```

This code works by iterating through each number in the range [l, r], and for each number, it checks if it is either not a prime (because it has more than 2 divisors) or it is a prime (because it has exactly 2 divisors). If the number is not a prime or it is a prime, it increments the result. At the end, it returns the count of numbers that are not special.

